  "instructions": [
    "Preheat a clay pot over low heat. ",
    "Add the duck legs, mint, parsley, garlic, lemon juice, olive oil, salt, and black pepper to the clay pot. ",
    "Cover the pot and cook for 2 hours. ",
    "While the duck cooks, prepare the flatbread dough. ",
    "Divide the dough into 4 equal pieces and roll each into a ball. ",
    "Heat the ghee in a small pan over medium heat. ",
    "Add a ball of dough to the pan and cook for 2-3 minutes on each side, until golden brown. ",
    "Repeat with the remaining dough balls. ",
    "Serve the duck with the garlic flatbread on the side. ",
    "Optional: garnish with additional mint and parsley. "
  ],
